   "text": "Cardiology Heart Failure Pharmacology HFrEF ARNI sacubitril neprilysin BNP NT-proBNP USMLE-style / MedKOS (PARADIGM-HF, 2022 AHA/ACC/HFSA HF guideline) A 58 year old man with HFrEF (LVEF 30%) on lisinopril, carvedilol, and spironolactone is transitioned to sacubitril/valsartan after a 36 hour washout of lisinopril. Two weeks later his exertional dyspnea has improved and he has lost 2 kg, but a repeat serum B type natriuretic peptide (BNP) is higher than his pretreatment value. His NT proBNP is lower than baseline. Which statement best explains this biomarker discordance? A. The rise in BNP indicates worsening congestion and the drug should be stopped B. Neprilysin inhibition reduces degradation of BNP, so BNP rises while NT proBNP (not a neprilysin substrate) better reflects clinical response C. The valsartan component causes aldosterone escape, secondarily raising BNP D. Sacubitril cross reacts with the BNP immunoassay, producing a falsely high value E. Anti drug antibodies to sacubitril have formed, elevating BNP Sacubitril은 neprilysin을 억제해 BNP(neprilysin 기질)의 분해를 줄여 BNP를 올리지만, NT proBNP는 neprilysin 기질이 아니어서 임상 호전과 함께 감소한다. 따라서 ARNI 치료 중 모니터링은 NT proBNP로 한다."
